### Welcome to the RAML API portal for the <a href="http://aws.amazon.com/s3" target="_blank"><img src="data:image/jpeg;base64," width="30px"> Amazon S3 Buckets API</a>! 

This portal provides 
- a [RAML spec](/apiplatform/repository/public/organizations/30/apis/8120/versions/8316/files/root) describing the Amazon S3 Buckets API in a clear, human- and machine-readable format
- [documentation](/apiplatform/popular/#/portals/apis/8120/versions/8316/pages/7016) of the Amazon S3 Buckets API auto-generated from the RAML spec
- the [documentation](/apiplatform/popular/#/portals/apis/8120/versions/8316/pages/7016) is live: you can make calls to the Amazon S3 Buckets API from the documentation
- live, documented usecases for the Amazon S3 Buckets API, provided as API notebooks, and exercising much of the Amazon S3 Buckets API

_This portal is built on the Anypoint Platform for APIs, using RAML version 0.8._

_For more information about RAML, see [http://raml.org](http://raml.org)._

_The API notebooks are all executable! Hit "enter" in any code cell to execute it (and all cells before it that have not executed yet), or scroll to the bottom of the notebook and click "Play notebook". For more information, see [http://apinotebook.com](http://apinotebook.com)._

---
### Please note:

This portal and its contents are not affiliated with Amazon S3. They are, however, useful for working with, and learning about, the Amazon S3 Buckets API.

The official developer API portal for Amazon S3 is at <a href="http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/APIRest.html​" target="_blank">http://docs.aws.amazon.com/AmazonS3/latest/API/APIRest.html​</a>
